HEADWORD: Hurons
<hw>Hu"rons</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing><it>sing.</it>
<singf>Huron</singf>.</sing> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A powerful and
warlike tribe of North American Indians of the Algonquin stock. They
formerly occupied the country between Lakes Huron, Erie, and Ontario,
but were nearly exterminated by the Five Nations about 1650.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

